{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:25.177760+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: c1890c5be9c4ff2cd786bd5114a559764919c79b)", "id": "lc_5916db48-843f-4a99-aea8-91ac875dcab7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n\"br\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git branch -vv\",\n  \"help\":\"show local branches\"},\n\"clean\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git clean -dfx\",\n  \"help\": \"remove all untracked files/folders\"},\n\"diff\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git diff\",\n  \"help\": \"git show differences\"},\n\"difftool\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git difftool\",\n  \"disable_async\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show differences using a tool\"\n  },\n\"fetch\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git fetch\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"fetch remote update\"\n  },\n\"last\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git log -1 HEAD\",\n  \"help\": \"show log information of HEAD\"\n  },\n\"lo\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git log --oneline -7\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show one-line log for the latest 7 commits\"\n  },\n\"log\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git log\",\n  \"disable_async\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show logs\"\n  },\n\"merge\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git merge @{u}\",\n  \"help\": \"merge remote updates\"\n  },\n\"mergetool\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git mergetool\",\n  \"disable_async\": true,\n  \"help\": \"merge updates with a tool\"\n  },\n\"patch\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git format-patch HEAD~\",\n  \"help\": \"make a patch\"\n  },\n\"pull\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git pull\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"pull remote updates\"\n  },\n\"push\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git push\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"push the local updates\"\n  },\n\"rebase\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git rebase\",\n  \"help\": \"rebase from master\"\n  },\n\"reflog\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git reflog\",\n  \"help\": \"show ref logs\"\n  },\n\"remote\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git remote -v\",\n  \"help\": \"show remote settings\"\n  },\n\"reset\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git reset\",\n  \"help\": \"reset repo(s)\"\n  },\n\"show\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git show\",\n  \"disable_async\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show detailed commit information\"\n  },\n\"stash\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git stash\",\n  \"help\": \"store uncommited changes\"\n  },\n\"stat\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git diff --stat\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show edit statistics\"\n  },\n\"st\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git status\",\n  \"allow_all\": true,\n  \"help\": \"show status\"\n  },\n\"tag\":{\n  \"cmd\": \"git tag -n\",\n  \"help\": \"show tags\"\n  }\n}\n", "id": "lc_bd9f1a5f-1bbe-4eb9-b77e-a12eaa21af0d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "544ede16-a7c6-4748-ae98-612f05d91e01", "tool_call_id": "call_00_vMe6UI0SxdR7zOPYdM4u8772", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:32.595196+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here are the subcommands registered in **`gita/cmds.json`** and the underlying `git` command each one runs:\n\n| Subcommand | Git command | allow_all | disable_async |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `br` | `git branch -vv` | | |\n| `clean` | `git clean -dfx` | | |\n| `diff` | `git diff` | | |\n| `difftool` | `git difftool` | | ✓ |\n| `fetch` | `git fetch` | ✓ | |\n| `last` | `git log -1 HEAD` | | |\n| `lo` | `git log --oneline -7` | ✓ | |\n| `log` | `git log` | | ✓ |\n| `merge` | `git merge @{u}` | | |\n| `mergetool` | `git mergetool` | | ✓ |\n| `patch` | `git format-patch HEAD~` | | |\n| `pull` | `git pull` | ✓ | |\n| `push` | `git push` | ✓ | |\n| `rebase` | `git rebase` | | |\n| `reflog` | `git reflog` | | |\n| `remote` | `git remote -v` | | |\n| `reset` | `git reset` | | |\n| `show` | `git show` | | ✓ |\n| `stash` | `git stash` | | |\n| `stat` | `git diff --stat` | ✓ | |\n| `st` | `git status` | ✓ | |\n| `tag` | `git tag -n` | | |\n\n**Summary of special flags:**\n\n- **`allow_all: true`** – 6 entries: `fetch`, `lo`, `pull`, `push`, `stat`, `st`.  \n  This flag typically signals that the command accepts extra user‑supplied arguments (i.e. passes them through to the underlying git command without restriction).\n\n- **`disable_async: true`** – 4 entries: `difftool`, `log`, `mergetool`, `show`.  \n  This flag tells the framework to run these commands synchronously rather than in the background, likely because they are interactive (e.g., launching a diff/merge tool) or produce output that should block the shell.\n\nAll other entries (e.g., `br`, `clean`, `diff`, `last`, `merge`, `patch`, `rebase`, `reflog`, `remote`, `reset`, `stash`, `tag`) use neither `allow_all` nor `disable_async`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 975, "prompt_tokens": 4517, "total_tokens": 5492, "completion_tokens_details": {